        "title": "refactor: move plugin state slices to sqlite",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Move Active Memory session toggles, Nostr bus/profile state, Phone Control armed state, and Microsoft Teams feedback learnings to SQLite-backed plugin state.\n- Keep runtime on the canonical store only: no runtime legacy JSON reads, deletes, dual-read, or lazy imports.\n- Add doctor-only migrations for the legacy files, including capacity checks, source archiving after verified import, Nostr v1 cursor normalization, Phone Control armed-state preservation, and Teams store-scoped learning keys.\n- Teach doctor contract discovery to load package-built `dist/doctor-contract-api.*` surfaces so npm plugins can ship these migrations.\n\n## Notes\n- Leaves session files and broader service/session state surfaces out of this slice.\n- Legacy Teams learning filenames that cannot be mapped through session metadata are left in place with a doctor warning instead of being archived under a guessed key.\n\n## Verification\n- `pnpm test extensions/active-memory/doctor-contract-api.test.ts extensions/phone-control/doctor-contract-api.test.ts extensions/nostr/doctor-contract-api.test.ts extensions/msteams/doctor-contract-api.test.ts extensions/nostr/src/nostr-state-store.test.ts extensions/active-memory/index.test.ts extensions/phone-control/index.test.ts extensions/msteams/src/feedback-reflection.test.ts`\n- `pnpm test src/plugins/doctor-contract-registry.load-paths.test.ts test/plugin-npm-runtime-build.test.ts`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode branch --base origin/main`\n",
